## Retrieval-Augmented-Generation (RAG)

    - Retrieval-Augmented-Generation (RAG) is a technique used to generate text based on a given context.
    - The most defining characteristic of RAG is that the context is typically a set of documents or a database, which the agentic framework then processes and generates a response based on the context, The generated text is typically used to answer a question or to complete a task.

